encodeTransaction

  • encodeTransaction(abi: FunctionEntry | ConstructorEntry, inputs: any[], options?: ResolveOptions): Promise<Options>
    • Defined in encoder/lib/encoders.ts:1028

    This method is asynchronous.

    This method works similarly to ProjectEncoder.encodeTransaction. However, instead of a Method object, it simply takes the ABI entry for the transaction being prepared. Note that the ABI must be one associated with this contract, or the function will not work.

    Note that use of the encoder for transactions to be sent to libraries is presently not supported and may have unreliable results. Limited support for this is planned for future versions.

    See ProjectEncoder.encodeTransaction for further details.

    Parameters

    • abi: FunctionEntry | ConstructorEntry

      The ABI entry for the transaction being prepared.

    • inputs: any[]
    • options: ResolveOptions = ...

    Returns Promise<Options>

forInstance

  • forInstance(address?: string): Promise<ContractInstanceEncoder>
    • Defined in encoder/lib/encoders.ts:1077

    This method is asynchronous.

    Constructs a contract instance encoder for a given instance of the contract this encoder is for.

    Parameters

      The address of the contract instance. If omitted, it will be autodetected. If an invalid address is provided, this method will throw an exception.

resolveAndEncode

  • resolveAndEncode(abis: FunctionEntry[], inputs: any[], options?: ResolveOptions): Promise<TxAndAbi>
    • Defined in encoder/lib/encoders.ts:1055

    This method is asynchronous.

    This method works similarly to ProjectEncoder.resolveAndEncode. However, instead of an array of Method objects, it simply takes an array of the ABI entries for the possible overloads. Only function ABI entries may be passed to this method, not constructor ABI entries. Note that the ABIs must be one associated with this contract, or the function will not work.

    Note that use of the encoder for transactions to be sent to libraries is presently not supported and may have unreliable results. Limited support for this is planned for future versions.

    See ProjectEncoder.resolveAndEncode for further details.

    Parameters

    • abis: FunctionEntry[]

      The ABI entries for the overloads to be resolved between.

    • inputs: any[]
    • options: ResolveOptions = ...

    Returns Promise<TxAndAbi>
